sub_title: Teacher in Swedish and Dutch, piano teacher, performer. Social, ambitious, imaginative, independent abstract thinker and knowledge driven performer.
summary:
As can be seen from my study and work history, my interests are very broad. I am more a generalist than a specialist and I find it difficult to restrict myself to a certain field. That's why a function for me ideally would be multidisciplanary or contain a variety of cases. I am creative and autonomous and also a perfectionist. I like to spawn ideas and need to be able to express this creativity and find this autonomy in my work. 

I enjoy working towards a shared goal. I thrive in an environment in which everyone works together and where everyone complements and stimulates each other. The goal ideally has a social purpose, for example reducing crime.  I really like to teach and transfer knowledge to people. Consequently, I am very good at giving informative presentations and I would really appreciate to contribute to the training of my coworkers. 

I have feeling for technology, be it only on a theoretical level. Getting things, code or devices to work is not my cup of tea, so trouble shooting and all kinds of programming functions - in fact all (implementing) I(C)T functions - are not what I am looking for. On the other hand I am very strong at abstract and logical-mathematical thinking. That's why a function that focuses on inventing, designing, planning, leading and coordinating suits me better than one focusing on implementing.  I am good at understanding cause and effect, thinking ahead multiple steps, creating plans and setting goals. Therefore I do well on a visionary position, in for example the intellectual, administrative or policy domain. Preferably I would also be able to put my language proficiency to use: an international environment would therefore be very suitable for me.
